Effective strategies for conflict resolution in the workplace include:

1. Open and honest communication;
2. Avoiding making assumptions;
3. Listening to and considering all points of view;
4. Respecting others' opinions;
5. Focusing on the issue rather than the person;
6. Finding common ground; and
7. Seeking clarification or further information when needed.

These strategies can help to address and resolve workplace conflict, improve relationships, and create a more positive work environment.

The C++ program below reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file:

```
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    ifstream fin("filename.txt");
    string word;
    int count = 0;
    while (fin >> word) {
        if (word == "cat") {
            count++;
        }
    }
    cout << "The word " << word << " was found " << count << " times in the text file." << endl;
